    <item>
      <title>What is String in Java</title>
      <link>https://darshkhatri.com/post/it/string/what-is-string-in-java/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 06 May 2021 00:41:20 +0530</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://darshkhatri.com/post/it/string/what-is-string-in-java/</guid>
      <description>
        
          &lt;h2 id=&#34;string-in-java&#34;&gt;String In Java&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In lemon language, we can identify String as a &lt;code&gt;Collection Of Characters&lt;/code&gt;.
But in java String identify as an object. We can declare String as an array In java as well as simple way as we write a String, But both the way String object collect that value as same.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Those two methods are below to declare a String.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;1-declare-string-using-array&#34;&gt;1. Declare String using array:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-java&#34; data-lang=&#34;java&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;kt&#34;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;[]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;sc&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;d&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;sc&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;a&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;sc&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;r&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;sc&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;s&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;sc&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;h&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;s&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4 id=&#34;2-declare-as-string-object&#34;&gt;2. Declare as String Object.&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-java&#34; data-lang=&#34;java&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;   &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;d&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;darsh&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt; The above two methods work similarly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;string-methods-in-java&#34;&gt;String Methods In Java&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The string has numerous method which we can use for simplifying logic. few of the method names and descriptions we can understand via the below matrix.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;thead&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Method Name&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Description&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Return Value&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/thead&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;isEmpty()&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;verify for emptry string&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;boolean&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;length()&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;return length of string&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;int&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;toLowerCase()&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;return string in lowercase&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;String&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;toUpperCase()&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;return string in uppercase&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;String&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;charAt(int index)&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;return char value of praticular index&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;char&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;how-many-ways-we-can-create-a-string-object&#34;&gt;How many ways we can create a String object?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is two way we can create an object of String as below :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;1-using-string-literal&#34;&gt;1. Using String literal&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;2-using-new-keyword&#34;&gt;2. Using new keyword&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;1-using-string-literal-1&#34;&gt;1. Using String literal&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The string has double quotes that identify as literal.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-java&#34; data-lang=&#34;java&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;   &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;d&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;darsh khatri&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Whenever you create a String object using String literal, so it will be found in JVM &lt;code&gt;String pool&lt;/code&gt;. If the value of String already exists and it returns a reference of that &lt;code&gt;String pool&lt;/code&gt; instance. Suppose if there has not a similar value of String in the String pool then, it will create a new object in JVM.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5 id=&#34;illustration&#34;&gt;Illustration:&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-java&#34; data-lang=&#34;java&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;   &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;d&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Peter Parker&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;   &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;k&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Peter Parker&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We have two objects as per the above pis of code. the first String value of the handler is   &#39;d&#39; and the second is   &#39;k&#39; . Both contain the same value and only one instance is created in JVM &lt;code&gt;String pool&lt;/code&gt;, and the other carriers as a reference of the first one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;2-create-string-using-new-keyword&#34;&gt;2. Create String using new keyword&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-java&#34; data-lang=&#34;java&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;   &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;s&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Darsh&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;);&lt;/span&gt; 
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;In the above case, JVM creates a new object of String in heap memory, and the String literal &lt;code&gt;Darsh&lt;/code&gt; will be in the String pool. The variable &#39;s&#39; is a handle or reference variable of that object.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;string-example-in-java&#34;&gt;String Example in Java&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-java&#34; data-lang=&#34;java&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt; 1&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;kd&#34;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;kd&#34;&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nc&#34;&gt;Employee&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt; 2&lt;/span&gt;        &lt;span class=&#34;kd&#34;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;kd&#34;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;kt&#34;&gt;void&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;args&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;[]){&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt; 3&lt;/span&gt;            &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;e1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Peter Parker&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt; 4&lt;/span&gt;            &lt;span class=&#34;kt&#34;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;[]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;sc&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;j&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;sc&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;o&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;sc&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;h&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;sc&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;n&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;};&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt; 5&lt;/span&gt;            &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;e2&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt; 6&lt;/span&gt;            &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;e3&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;kate&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt; 7&lt;/span&gt;            &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;System&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;na&#34;&gt;out&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;na&#34;&gt;println&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;e1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;  
&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt; 8&lt;/span&gt;            &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;System&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;na&#34;&gt;out&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;na&#34;&gt;println&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;e2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;  
&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt; 9&lt;/span&gt;            &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;System&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;na&#34;&gt;out&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;na&#34;&gt;println&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;e3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;        &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;   
&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;11&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4 id=&#34;output-is-&#34;&gt;Output is :&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-java&#34; data-lang=&#34;java&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;   &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;Peter&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;Parker&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;   &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;john&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;   &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;kate&lt;/span&gt; 
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;conclusion-points&#34;&gt;Conclusion Points:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collection of characters called String.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;String is Object.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We can create String two-way. 1) String literal and 2) Using new keyword.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If Literal String have a similar value so, a new reference is not created in JVM
&lt;code&gt;string pool&lt;/code&gt;. It uses the reference of duplicate value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;String has various methods so, we can use that for different types of operation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

        
